In this update:
[1] Cholera - Cuba (Cienfuegos Province)
[2] Cholera - Mexico (Veracruz, Hidalgo)

******
[1] Cholera - Cuba (Cienfuegos Province)
Date: Sat 23 Nov 2013
Source: Cubanet [in Spanish, trans. & summ., edited]
http://www.cubanet.org/otros/alarma-sanitaria-por-colera-en-cumanayagua/


A cholera alarm went out this week in Cumanayagua (Cienfuegos Province). This is the 2nd outbreak in the province so far in 2013.

Up to the morning of 21 Nov 2013, 64 cases positive for a cholera rapid test, including 1 death, had been reported, an undetermined number of patients is in critical condition, and more than 100 persons affected by profuse diarrhea are awaiting the results of the tests.

The health crisis has prompted the visit of senior officials from the Ministry of Health. Similarly, this has led to the mobilization of government officials at different levels, business managers, and health workers as well as the concentration of logistical resources in the hardest hit areas of the province.

Health brigades in vehicles with loudspeakers travelled through streets and avenues, informing people about the sanitary measures to implement, that is, the purchase of hypochlorite from the network of pharmacies and disinfectants sold in some state-run stores.

At the moment nobody dares to predict the time it would take to eliminate the epidemic, as it is far from being controlled.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-ESP
<promed-esp@promedmail.org>

[This is a nongovernment report. ProMED-mail awaits formal reporting of these cases. - Mod.LL

